turn.3: What happened to the railway in 1880?
turn.4: The railway was taken over by the Great Eastern Railway in 1880, with the locomotives joining the GER stock list.
turn.5: When was the last time they were used?
turn.6: The Sharp locomotives being scrapped in 1891 and the tank engines in the late 1880s.
turn.8: The line was lifted after closure.
turn.9: Are there any other interesting aspects about this article?
turn.10: The route either side of Stow Bedon station has been removed, and the station site levelled.
turn.12: The section of line between Stow Bedon and Wretham was intended to be used for a new road, and Stow Bedon station was demolished as part of this plan.
